cts of coercion), this book also discusses ethnic enclaves (products of choice) in cities like Belfast, Toronto, Amsterdam, and New York. Since 9/11 the ghetto-enclave distinction has become blurred as crime and disorder have emanated from both European immigrant ethnic enclaves and America's ghettos. The contributors offer a variety of tools for addressing the problems of racial and income segregation, including school integration, area-based "fair share" housing requirements, place-based mixed-income housing development, and expanded demand-side residential subsidy options such as housing vouchers. By exploring these alternatives and their consequences, Desegregating the City provides the basis for a combination of flexible antisegregation strategies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aInner citieszUnited States. 0aSegregationzUnited States. 4aAfrican American Studies : African American Studies. 4aPublic Policy : Urban and Regional Planning. 4aSociology : Urban Sociology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Urban.2bisacsh1 aBanerjee, Tridib, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoal, Frederick W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEspino, N. Ariel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriedman, Samantha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuchzermeyer, Marie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMabin, Alan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarcuse, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeach, Ceri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPearce-Oroz, Glenn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPendall, Rolf, econtributor.4